<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">No, this is the original text by Sir Arthur Conan Doyle. &apos;A Scandal in Bohemia&apos; is the first short story in the collection published as &apos;The Adventure<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">No, this is the original text by Sir Arthur Conan Doyle. 'A Scandal in Bohemia' is the first short story in the collection published as 'The Adventures of Sherlock Holmes'. It is the third insallment of the Holmes-Saga after the full-length novels 'A Study in Scarlet' and 'The Sign of Four'.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
