        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer740725861" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11839786315263679819">This was, quite naturally, the first Sherlock Holmes story I ever read, and I was so confused by Irene, thinking I&apos;d somehow missed a preceding story. Kind of fell into the narrative anyway, and it didn&apos;t matter that I couldn&apos;t quite figure out some of the details.<br/><br/>This is one of the more well-known of the Holmes collection because it&apos;s unique, and because it introduces us to some rather important characters. It easily cemented my love for this eccentric detective and I quickly devoured the rest </span>
  <span id="freeText11839786315263679819" style="display:none">This was, quite naturally, the first Sherlock Holmes story I ever read, and I was so confused by Irene, thinking I'd somehow missed a preceding story. Kind of fell into the narrative anyway, and it didn't matter that I couldn't quite figure out some of the details.<br /><br />This is one of the more well-known of the Holmes collection because it's unique, and because it introduces us to some rather important characters. It easily cemented my love for this eccentric detective and I quickly devoured the rest of the Sherlock Holmes adventures after that.<br /><br />A great one to start with.</span>
